    "This particular method is called inverse reinforcement learning introduced by Ng and Russell (2000), and suggested as a path towards artificial virtuous agents byBerberich and Diepold (2018).",
    "For instance, following empirical risk minimization, we might define the optimal h * as the hypothesis among H for which the risk of misclassification is minimal.",
